WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:06.000
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:17.829 --> 00:00:21.490
<i>[Episode 3]</i>
Joon, you're here to help me?

3
00:00:21.490 --> 00:00:23.006
You came on your own?

4
00:00:23.006 --> 00:00:27.348
So, you were worried about me,
weren't you?

5
00:00:27.348 --> 00:00:30.063
No, I'm here because of money.

6
00:00:30.063 --> 00:00:31.269
Huh?

7
00:00:31.269 --> 00:00:33.302
<i>Joon.</i>

8
00:00:34.066 --> 00:00:39.358
<i>Don't make important decisions
in your life based on money.</i>

9
00:00:40.790 --> 00:00:43.090
You know, the world...

10
00:00:44.492 --> 00:00:47.257
it doesn't always work out
the way you think it will.

11
00:00:48.632 --> 00:00:53.531
I felt I had no choice and ended up
making a cowardly decision.

12
00:00:55.362 --> 00:00:59.027
I hope you don't live the way I do, Joon.

13
00:01:00.710 --> 00:01:03.614
<i>I didn't know what
he had meant by that back then.</i>

14
00:01:04.167 --> 00:01:06.269
<i>Dad, you were right.</i>

15
00:01:06.269 --> 00:01:09.112
<i>The world doesn't always
work out the way I want.</i>

16
00:01:11.623 --> 00:01:13.493
<i>Young Ho got very injured.</i>

17
00:01:13.493 --> 00:01:15.563
<i>I need 10 million won.
What can I do?</i>

18
00:01:15.563 --> 00:01:18.462
<i>The only person
your mom can ask is you.</i>

19
00:01:29.611 --> 00:01:31.075
I'm busy enough living my own life.

20
00:01:31.099 --> 00:01:33.069
Why would I worry about
some rich guy like you?

21
00:01:33.069 --> 00:01:36.110
I came because of money.
You have a lot of money.

22
00:01:36.849 --> 00:01:38.562
How much do you need?

23
00:01:38.562 --> 00:01:41.389
In return for getting you out of here...

24
00:01:42.020 --> 00:01:44.300
I think I'll charge
about five million won.

25
00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:45.401
How about it?

26
00:01:46.081 --> 00:01:48.576
- Five million won?
- Yes, five million.

27
00:01:51.049 --> 00:01:52.680
Is that too much?

28
00:01:55.080 --> 00:01:58.914
In return, I have a condition too.

29
00:01:58.914 --> 00:02:00.263
What's the condition?

30
00:02:00.263 --> 00:02:05.156
Until I can go home...
will you stay by my side, Joon?

31
00:02:06.872 --> 00:02:09.623
I have to be on the run for now.

32
00:02:09.623 --> 00:02:13.389
I'll pay you the average salary
of a Gangsu Group secretary.

33
00:02:13.895 --> 00:02:16.246
<i>How frustrated do you think
I am to be doing this?</i>

34
00:02:16.246 --> 00:02:18.539
<i>Think of it as helping me out.</i>

35
00:02:18.539 --> 00:02:20.270
<i>Isn't there somewhere
you could get money?</i>

36
00:02:21.028 --> 00:02:22.131
<i>Joon.</i>

37
00:02:23.312 --> 00:02:27.354
<i>Don't make important decisions
in your life...</i>

38
00:02:28.364 --> 00:02:30.074
based on money.

39
00:02:36.223 --> 00:02:37.544
What do you think about my offer?

40
00:02:39.745 --> 00:02:42.354
<i>But, Dad...
Do you know what?</i>

41
00:02:43.153 --> 00:02:47.876
<i>Important decisions
don't exist in my life.</i>

42
00:02:48.433 --> 00:02:50.735
<i>I'm just trying to survive, day by day.</i>

43
00:02:55.231 --> 00:02:56.322
I'm in.

44
00:02:59.338 --> 00:03:03.329
Then is today our first day?

45
00:03:06.409 --> 00:03:08.368
Yes, our first day.

46
00:03:09.579 --> 00:03:10.717
<i>First day?</i>

47
00:03:10.742 --> 00:03:12.530
What are you guys talking about?

48
00:03:12.530 --> 00:03:14.308
Byun Hyuk! Hey, Byun Hyuk!

49
00:03:15.194 --> 00:03:16.936
There's a back exit in the garage.

50
00:03:16.936 --> 00:03:18.612
Wait for us there.

51
00:03:18.612 --> 00:03:20.349
Wait, a back exit?

52
00:03:20.879 --> 00:03:22.258
Hey, Baek Joon.

53
00:03:27.311 --> 00:03:28.992
We're heading down now.

54
00:03:29.740 --> 00:03:32.610
Get in. Hurry, hurry.

55
00:03:47.858 --> 00:03:49.357
Excuse me.

56
00:05:04.293 --> 00:05:06.709
Joon? We're alone, right?

57
00:05:06.709 --> 00:05:09.194
- Are we in the elevator?
- Be quiet!

58
00:05:16.009 --> 00:05:17.572
I'll join you.

59
00:05:26.165 --> 00:05:27.355
What's going on?

60
00:05:44.709 --> 00:05:46.475
You know that suite room?

61
00:05:46.475 --> 00:05:47.699
Yes?

62
00:05:48.137 --> 00:05:51.959
Is this the guest staying there?

63
00:05:51.959 --> 00:05:55.439
Oh... I really don't know.

64
00:05:55.439 --> 00:05:58.300
Really? Please take a closer look.

65
00:05:58.300 --> 00:05:59.574
Why look again?

66
00:05:59.574 --> 00:06:02.026
It's my first time seeing that person.

67
00:06:21.930 --> 00:06:23.072
Sorry.

68
00:06:23.653 --> 00:06:24.716
It's all right.

69
00:06:30.812 --> 00:06:33.565
Oh, there must be a mosquito in here.

70
00:06:36.281 --> 00:06:37.615
Oh my.

71
00:06:38.293 --> 00:06:39.887
It's very hot.

72
00:06:39.889 --> 00:06:44.259
If you happen to see this guest,
could you please contact...

73
00:06:44.259 --> 00:06:46.858
Sorry, but it's against
the hotel rules to do so.

74
00:06:46.858 --> 00:06:49.014
Still, if you could cooperate...

75
00:06:49.014 --> 00:06:52.336
We're not allowed to talk about
guests to external parties.

76
00:06:52.336 --> 00:06:54.103
Think of it as doing a good thing...

77
00:06:54.103 --> 00:06:55.593
I said that I can't!

78
00:07:06.795 --> 00:07:10.156
I'm sorry... sorry.

79
00:07:51.307 --> 00:07:52.610
Hold up, there.

80
00:07:54.149 --> 00:07:55.322
Wait!

81
00:07:58.461 --> 00:07:59.692
Hold on!

82
00:08:02.440 --> 00:08:03.846
Hey!

83
00:08:03.846 --> 00:08:06.011
Move. Get out of the way.

84
00:09:11.711 --> 00:09:12.836
Excuse me.

85
00:09:13.596 --> 00:09:15.567
What are you doing here?

86
00:09:16.327 --> 00:09:19.128
You can't just come in here.

87
00:09:19.128 --> 00:09:20.407
Sorry.

88
00:09:27.677 --> 00:09:29.215
- Where is he?
- Jae Hoon!

89
00:09:29.215 --> 00:09:30.902
Oh, where is Kwon Jae Hoon?

90
00:09:30.903 --> 00:09:32.721
Jae Hoon, Jae Hoon!

91
00:09:32.721 --> 00:09:34.250
- Hey, hey!
- Jae Hoon!

92
00:09:39.014 --> 00:09:40.225
Get in!

93
00:09:52.943 --> 00:09:55.361
You should've turned
your phone off beforehand.

94
00:09:55.361 --> 00:09:57.932
Who would message me at a time like that?

95
00:09:58.432 --> 00:10:00.552
<i>Hyuk, why can't I contact you?</i>

96
00:10:00.552 --> 00:10:03.216
<i>Let's meet up and talk. Huh, huh?</i>

97
00:10:03.216 --> 00:10:05.123
Chae Ri, why are you doing this to me?

98
00:10:05.123 --> 00:10:06.625
Chae Ri? Who's that?

99
00:10:06.625 --> 00:10:08.104
- You don't need to know.
- You don't need to know.

100
00:10:08.332 --> 00:10:11.442
Anyway, Baek Joon.
Why did you suddenly get involved?

101
00:10:11.442 --> 00:10:13.341
What's this about "first day"? Tell me.

102
00:10:13.341 --> 00:10:16.089
Oh, Joon agreed to be
my personal secretary.

103
00:10:16.089 --> 00:10:17.298
Who said you can?

104
00:10:17.298 --> 00:10:19.115
She's my secretary,
so it's up to me.

105
00:10:19.115 --> 00:10:22.255
Hey, you're not in the position
to make decisions like that.

106
00:10:22.255 --> 00:10:24.264
I'm the one who's looking after you.

107
00:10:24.264 --> 00:10:26.265
I have to take responsibility
if anything happens.

108
00:10:26.265 --> 00:10:27.816
- So, I can't?
- You can't.

109
00:10:27.816 --> 00:10:29.634
That agreement is void.
There's no contract either.

110
00:10:29.634 --> 00:10:31.806
Don't you know that
verbal contracts are binding too?

111
00:10:31.806 --> 00:10:34.047
Yeah, we shook on it too, right?

112
00:10:34.047 --> 00:10:36.128
Joon, you can't handle Hyuk.

113
00:10:36.128 --> 00:10:37.620
You do it, so why can't I?

114
00:10:37.620 --> 00:10:40.000
Drunk driving, disturbance
in clubs, public urination...

115
00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:41.158
Can you handle that?

116
00:10:41.158 --> 00:10:42.558
What? Public urination?

117
00:10:42.558 --> 00:10:44.096
What happened with that was...

118
00:10:44.096 --> 00:10:45.482
I don't care. That's nothing.

119
00:10:45.482 --> 00:10:47.163
- Really?
- You still can't.

120
00:10:47.163 --> 00:10:48.332
I won't allow it.

121
00:10:48.332 --> 00:10:50.581
Are you looking down on me,
by any chance?

122
00:10:50.581 --> 00:10:53.910
Why do you always twist
my words around like that?

123
00:10:53.910 --> 00:10:55.052
Is it an inferiority complex?

124
00:10:55.052 --> 00:10:56.259
Inferiority?

125
00:10:56.259 --> 00:10:59.361
Hey, do you think anyone who doesn't
work for a big company feels inferior?

126
00:10:59.361 --> 00:11:01.437
Why bring up a big company?

127
00:11:01.437 --> 00:11:03.302
Why bring up inferiority?

128
00:11:03.302 --> 00:11:05.621
Hey, I'm sorry!
Sorry to interrupt here.

129
00:11:05.621 --> 00:11:07.509
Joon is an employee of
Gangsu Group today.

130
00:11:07.509 --> 00:11:10.078
Joon, your inferiority
can go to the dogs.

131
00:11:10.078 --> 00:11:11.548
- Stay out of it!
- Stay out of it!

132
00:11:12.828 --> 00:11:15.808
Do you think we would've escaped
the hotel if weren't for me?

133
00:11:15.809 --> 00:11:17.859
I worked really hard
to get rid of that cop.

134
00:11:17.859 --> 00:11:20.433
I had to go endure
someone's gas too.

135
00:11:20.700 --> 00:11:22.749
Joon is right about that.

136
00:11:22.960 --> 00:11:25.570
The hotel escape was perfect.

137
00:11:26.360 --> 00:11:28.850
If it was so perfect,
why is a police car following us?

138
00:11:28.850 --> 00:11:30.283
- A police car?
- What?

139
00:11:39.450 --> 00:11:41.245
What do we do?

140
00:11:46.892 --> 00:11:48.509
He followed us.

141
00:11:48.509 --> 00:11:50.159
Step on it, Jae Hoon!

142
00:11:54.049 --> 00:11:55.701
Hold on tight.

143
00:12:03.191 --> 00:12:05.173
What's with him? Is he a terminator?

144
00:12:05.173 --> 00:12:06.325
Why does he keep coming?

145
00:12:06.325 --> 00:12:07.965
What are you doing? Go faster.

146
00:12:07.965 --> 00:12:09.879
Jae Hoon is like that. He never speeds.

147
00:12:09.879 --> 00:12:11.537
Look at him now.
He's still not speeding.

148
00:12:11.537 --> 00:12:15.216
You want to leave your picture on the
speeding cameras when you're on the run?

149
00:12:15.216 --> 00:12:17.556
This isn't going to work.
Take a right around that corner.

150
00:12:17.556 --> 00:12:19.275
We'll get off at that intersection.

151
00:12:19.275 --> 00:12:21.125
I'll stop once I turn
so you can get out.

152
00:12:21.125 --> 00:12:23.337
No! I want to get out with Joon too.

153
00:12:23.337 --> 00:12:25.208
You're a wanted man.
Why would you go with her?

154
00:12:25.208 --> 00:12:26.485
He could safer with me.

155
00:12:26.485 --> 00:12:28.092
I'm his personal secretary
starting today.

156
00:12:28.092 --> 00:12:30.341
He's a third generation rich guy.
You're just a section chief.

157
00:12:30.341 --> 00:12:31.821
- You can't say no.
- Just a section chief?

158
00:12:31.821 --> 00:12:34.633
Can you stop referring to me
as the third generation rich guy?

159
00:12:48.847 --> 00:12:50.692
He's telling us to stop, right?

160
00:12:54.355 --> 00:12:56.365
Step on it, Jae Hoon!

161
00:13:01.615 --> 00:13:03.092
What should we do?

162
00:13:03.092 --> 00:13:05.393
Should we all get caught,
or will you let us out?

163
00:13:05.393 --> 00:13:07.265
- Jae Hoon!
- Hurry.

164
00:13:07.265 --> 00:13:09.138
Gosh, seriously!

165
00:13:30.514 --> 00:13:32.028
Move your car!

166
00:13:34.018 --> 00:13:35.357
Mister, move your car!

167
00:13:57.711 --> 00:14:01.359
<i>Vehicle license plate 7684.
7684, pull over.</i>

168
00:14:02.018 --> 00:14:03.947
<i>7684, pull over.</i>

169
00:14:04.488 --> 00:14:05.817
<i>Pull over.</i>

170
00:15:00.159 --> 00:15:01.508
What's the problem?

171
00:15:02.009 --> 00:15:03.798
Please cooperate for a moment.

172
00:15:05.110 --> 00:15:06.788
Could you please open your trunk?

173
00:15:24.582 --> 00:15:26.062
Where did they go?

174
00:15:26.062 --> 00:15:27.208
What do you mean?

175
00:15:27.208 --> 00:15:29.883
You picked up some people
from the hotel earlier.

176
00:15:29.883 --> 00:15:32.572
Picked up some people?
I never did that.

177
00:15:32.572 --> 00:15:35.587
If you're done with everything,
may I get going?

178
00:15:38.746 --> 00:15:42.062
You went over the speed limit.
May I see your ID?

179
00:15:42.062 --> 00:15:43.778
I don't think I was speeding.

180
00:15:43.999 --> 00:15:45.442
You were speeding.

181
00:15:46.428 --> 00:15:49.288
If I was speeding,
there was a camera.

182
00:15:49.288 --> 00:15:50.950
I'm sure I'll get a ticket notice.

183
00:15:50.950 --> 00:15:53.769
I'll be careful in the future.
I'll be going, then.

184
00:16:08.870 --> 00:16:10.523
Oh, what a relief.

185
00:16:10.523 --> 00:16:11.778
Oh...

186
00:16:21.721 --> 00:16:23.698
It's finally just the two of us.

187
00:16:23.698 --> 00:16:25.408
Where are we going now?

188
00:16:25.408 --> 00:16:28.673
A perfect place for
a third generation rich guy to hide.

189
00:16:28.673 --> 00:16:30.127
Where's that?

190
00:16:53.392 --> 00:16:55.618
This is the good hiding place
you were talking about?

191
00:16:55.618 --> 00:16:58.618
Where else is a better hiding place
for a third generation rich guy?

192
00:16:58.618 --> 00:17:02.381
I'd rather go to prison than here.

193
00:17:02.381 --> 00:17:05.586
Yeah? Do what you want, then.

194
00:17:08.723 --> 00:17:10.296
Let's go to Han River instead.

195
00:17:10.296 --> 00:17:11.788
I have a yacht there.

196
00:17:11.788 --> 00:17:13.986
There aren't many people there,
so it's perfect.

197
00:17:13.986 --> 00:17:16.227
They even have champagne.
It's sparkling and--

198
00:17:16.227 --> 00:17:18.752
I'm late, right. I'm so sorry.

199
00:17:18.752 --> 00:17:20.659
- Joon.
- I'm sorry.

200
00:17:23.298 --> 00:17:25.880
Mister Byun, you came back.

201
00:17:25.880 --> 00:17:29.221
I thought you'd quit after a day.
You're tougher than I thought.

202
00:17:29.221 --> 00:17:31.394
I'm glad you came back, young man.

203
00:17:31.394 --> 00:17:35.461
Of course, a young man
shouldn't give up after one day.

204
00:17:35.461 --> 00:17:37.695
Please stop that, Madam.

205
00:17:37.695 --> 00:17:40.673
Why do you keep touching
the butt of someone's precious son?

206
00:17:42.863 --> 00:17:43.913
That's right.

207
00:17:43.913 --> 00:17:46.682
I'm not the kind of person
who should work in a place like this.

208
00:17:46.682 --> 00:17:47.855
A place like this?

209
00:17:47.855 --> 00:17:49.172
Today, we're doing bricks.

210
00:17:49.173 --> 00:17:53.374
In order to move all those bricks today,
we can't waste any time.

211
00:17:54.154 --> 00:17:55.873
B... bricks?

212
00:18:02.179 --> 00:18:03.657
This isn't right, is it?

213
00:18:03.657 --> 00:18:06.167
Do I have to do this?
Please save me.

214
00:18:06.679 --> 00:18:08.028
You blend right in.

215
00:18:08.028 --> 00:18:09.608
It really suits you to be here.

216
00:18:09.608 --> 00:18:10.772
- Work hard.
- Work hard.

217
00:18:10.772 --> 00:18:12.962
- Work hard.
- Hurry up and get to it.

218
00:18:13.744 --> 00:18:14.933
What?

219
00:18:26.592 --> 00:18:28.170
What do I do?

220
00:18:28.750 --> 00:18:30.363
I must be crazy.

221
00:18:31.509 --> 00:18:34.183
I helped a wanted criminal escape.

222
00:18:35.593 --> 00:18:40.376
Even if I needed money,
I shouldn't help a criminal.

223
00:18:40.376 --> 00:18:43.884
I held his hand in front a cop
and helped him run.

224
00:18:43.884 --> 00:18:46.652
At this rate,
will I end up being arrested?

225
00:18:55.834 --> 00:18:57.952
<i>[Kwon Jae Hoon]</i>

226
00:19:01.419 --> 00:19:03.282
What? What is it?

227
00:19:03.282 --> 00:19:05.688
Where are you right now? Are you safe?

228
00:19:05.688 --> 00:19:06.953
Don't worry.

229
00:19:06.953 --> 00:19:09.042
I'm taking good care of the
third generation rich guy.

230
00:19:09.042 --> 00:19:11.204
Tell me where you are.
I'll pick him up now.

231
00:19:11.204 --> 00:19:13.772
You don't need to do that.
I'm busy, so I have to hang up.

232
00:19:14.634 --> 00:19:15.752
Busy?

233
00:19:17.512 --> 00:19:19.689
What are they doing that they're busy?

234
00:19:19.689 --> 00:19:22.196
So, where's Hyuk?

235
00:19:22.196 --> 00:19:24.214
He escaped for now.

236
00:19:24.214 --> 00:19:25.553
He escaped for now?

237
00:19:26.323 --> 00:19:27.393
Where to?

238
00:19:28.084 --> 00:19:31.694
I used a third party to help out.

239
00:19:31.694 --> 00:19:34.789
That person will contact me
once he arrives at a safe place

240
00:19:34.789 --> 00:19:35.843
so don't worry.

241
00:19:35.843 --> 00:19:37.299
What third party?

242
00:19:39.125 --> 00:19:44.039
It's temporary, so don't worry about it.

243
00:19:47.925 --> 00:19:49.003
Come in.

244
00:19:52.323 --> 00:19:53.654
It's all ready to go.

245
00:19:59.463 --> 00:20:00.555
Didn't I tell you?

246
00:20:01.394 --> 00:20:03.092
We're having a press conference.

247
00:20:16.021 --> 00:20:17.030
It's me.

248
00:20:17.464 --> 00:20:20.413
I need you to trace an IP for me,
as soon as possible.

249
00:20:20.413 --> 00:20:22.251
Make sure you keep this secure.

250
00:20:37.523 --> 00:20:38.525
Joon.

251
00:20:38.525 --> 00:20:41.688
What are you doing?
Move... move.

252
00:20:42.192 --> 00:20:43.878
- Okay.
- Move.

253
00:20:47.099 --> 00:20:49.276
Oh, it stings so much!

254
00:20:49.276 --> 00:20:52.106
Joon, Joon! Joon, Joon, Joon!

255
00:20:52.106 --> 00:20:54.696
