00:39:55.313 --> 00:39:57.201
Then say it's not attempted murder.

509
00:39:57.201 --> 00:39:58.804
You little...

510
00:39:58.804 --> 00:40:00.490
Oh, what's this?

511
00:40:04.251 --> 00:40:05.425
Who are you?

512
00:40:05.425 --> 00:40:06.900
He... he's my friend.

513
00:40:06.900 --> 00:40:07.998
Jae Hoon.

514
00:40:13.106 --> 00:40:14.266
Let go now.

515
00:40:15.965 --> 00:40:17.836
Why don't we go and talk?

516
00:40:26.971 --> 00:40:28.797
He looks very handsome.

517
00:40:28.797 --> 00:40:30.487
Is he Joon's boyfriend?

518
00:40:30.487 --> 00:40:33.141
No, he's my friend.

519
00:40:33.141 --> 00:40:36.153
He must work in a good place.
He looks very clean cut.

520
00:40:36.153 --> 00:40:38.543
Madam Ahn, you're really something.

521
00:40:38.543 --> 00:40:41.704
He could end up at the police station
and you're thinking about his looks?

522
00:40:41.704 --> 00:40:44.585
Don't worry. That won't happen.

523
00:40:44.585 --> 00:40:47.434
Jae Hoon is an expert.

524
00:40:47.963 --> 00:40:50.659
- An expert.
- Yes, an expert.

525
00:40:51.240 --> 00:40:52.476
Gosh...

526
00:40:54.775 --> 00:40:59.003
Treatment cost and even money
for emotional distress damages.

527
00:40:59.003 --> 00:41:01.608
I will give you more
than enough settlement money.

528
00:41:02.181 --> 00:41:04.067
What are you talking about?

529
00:41:04.067 --> 00:41:06.454
We're the ones who need damages
for emotional distress.

530
00:41:06.454 --> 00:41:09.958
He always shows up during lunch
and rushes everyone.

531
00:41:09.958 --> 00:41:13.028
He ignores all labor laws and
fires people whenever he wants.

532
00:41:13.028 --> 00:41:15.510
We're the ones who deserve damages
for emotional distress.

533
00:41:15.510 --> 00:41:19.820
Let's not leave any paperwork
and make things complicated.

534
00:41:19.820 --> 00:41:21.583
CEO Min Sung Ho.

535
00:41:28.661 --> 00:41:31.143
- Do you know me?
- No.

536
00:41:31.143 --> 00:41:32.721
Not very well.

537
00:41:32.721 --> 00:41:34.969
So I looked into you on my way here.

538
00:41:34.971 --> 00:41:40.161
You have a few paper companies
besides this construction company.

539
00:41:46.530 --> 00:41:48.398
That's all for tax evasion, isn't it?

540
00:41:50.389 --> 00:41:54.094
You've used the supposed wages to
make a nice slush fund for yourself.

541
00:41:59.358 --> 00:42:00.436
Wow.

542
00:42:06.219 --> 00:42:09.608
You punk... who are you?

543
00:42:10.909 --> 00:42:12.768
There's no need for you to know.

544
00:42:14.329 --> 00:42:15.878
Why don't you settle?

545
00:42:24.132 --> 00:42:26.507
Well, we understand then.

546
00:42:26.507 --> 00:42:27.601
Thank you.

547
00:42:39.608 --> 00:42:41.682
He really is skilled.

548
00:42:41.684 --> 00:42:43.510
He wasn't even in there for 10 minutes.

549
00:42:43.536 --> 00:42:45.724
How did he get CEO Min to stay quiet?

550
00:42:45.724 --> 00:42:48.454
What did I tell you?
I told you Jae Hoon would resolve it!

551
00:42:48.454 --> 00:42:51.204
That's the level my friend is at.

552
00:42:52.751 --> 00:42:54.900
What the heck were you thinking?

553
00:42:54.900 --> 00:42:57.641
- Huh?
- What happened with the brick?

554
00:42:57.641 --> 00:43:00.871
Oh, it was actually because
of a dandelion seed flower.

555
00:43:00.871 --> 00:43:02.652
- What?
- Oh...

556
00:43:02.652 --> 00:43:05.244
It had grown even in the cement.

557
00:43:05.244 --> 00:43:07.762
You know how I like to blow on the seeds.

558
00:43:08.782 --> 00:43:10.789
I had no idea there was a brick there.

559
00:43:10.789 --> 00:43:13.425
So, it was just an accident.

560
00:43:13.425 --> 00:43:14.496
Accident.

561
00:43:15.094 --> 00:43:18.016
Just like drunk driving and
the club disturbances were?

562
00:43:18.016 --> 00:43:20.585
Of course, they all were accidents.

563
00:43:20.585 --> 00:43:23.311
The public urination
and Yeon Hee were accidents too?

564
00:43:25.231 --> 00:43:27.512
Joon, why are you being scary?

565
00:43:27.512 --> 00:43:29.273
They really were all accidents.

566
00:43:33.237 --> 00:43:35.175
- I was crazy.
- Huh?

567
00:43:35.175 --> 00:43:38.829
No matter how much I need the money,
I shouldn't have agreed to help you.

568
00:43:39.880 --> 00:43:41.139
Why are you being this way?

569
00:43:41.139 --> 00:43:43.621
Forget it. Let's end it here.

570
00:43:43.621 --> 00:43:44.920
End it?

571
00:43:45.492 --> 00:43:47.969
- What?
- I won't be your personal secretary.

572
00:43:47.969 --> 00:43:50.467
Let's just head down our own paths.

573
00:43:53.849 --> 00:43:54.947
Joon!

574
00:43:56.952 --> 00:43:58.289
That's enough.

575
00:43:59.088 --> 00:44:00.880
Joon seems really angry.

576
00:44:00.880 --> 00:44:03.068
Stop and get in the car!

577
00:44:21.829 --> 00:44:23.172
<i>[Mom]</i>

578
00:44:31.018 --> 00:44:32.373
<i>[Mom]</i>

579
00:44:37.931 --> 00:44:41.489
Mom, I'm sorry.

580
00:44:42.672 --> 00:44:44.311
I can't give you that money.

581
00:44:45.548 --> 00:44:47.550
So, stop calling me.

582
00:45:06.246 --> 00:45:08.666
Why does everything I do
turn out this way?

583
00:45:09.983 --> 00:45:12.414
Even if someone set out to cause trouble

584
00:45:12.414 --> 00:45:14.503
it'd be hard to cause as much as you.

585
00:45:14.503 --> 00:45:17.574
I just wanted to
let the dandelion seeds fly.

586
00:45:19.594 --> 00:45:21.554
Was that so wrong?

587
00:45:22.333 --> 00:45:25.349
You nearly ended up at the police
station because of dandelion seeds.

588
00:45:25.349 --> 00:45:27.753
Those people almost
lost their livelihoods.

589
00:45:27.753 --> 00:45:29.427
Of course, she'd be mad.

590
00:45:31.393 --> 00:45:32.949
I was wrong.

591
00:45:34.483 --> 00:45:35.909
What do I do now?

592
00:45:36.722 --> 00:45:40.987
What do I do in order
to get Joon to forgive me?

593
00:45:44.094 --> 00:45:45.253
Dream on.

594
00:45:45.253 --> 00:45:47.563
Once Joon is done, she means it.

595
00:45:47.563 --> 00:45:50.907
It didn't even make sense that she
agreed to be your personal secretary.

596
00:45:50.907 --> 00:45:55.088
Unless she loses her mind,
she will probably never do it again.

597
00:45:55.956 --> 00:45:57.405
Is that right?

598
00:46:07.597 --> 00:46:09.146
This is from your mom.

599
00:46:18.831 --> 00:46:19.918
Jae Hoon!

600
00:46:19.918 --> 00:46:21.856
- What now?
- Joon.

601
00:46:21.856 --> 00:46:23.766
How to make her not angry...

602
00:46:23.766 --> 00:46:25.730
I thought of a way.

603
00:46:36.204 --> 00:46:37.630
Don't come here anymore.

604
00:46:37.630 --> 00:46:38.983
- What?
- What?

605
00:46:39.992 --> 00:46:41.949
What do you mean by that?

606
00:46:41.949 --> 00:46:43.434
Stop coming tomorrow?

607
00:46:43.434 --> 00:46:44.753
It's CEO Min's orders.

608
00:46:44.753 --> 00:46:47.612
The three of you and Baek Joon
should not come in.

609
00:46:47.612 --> 00:46:51.384
Foreman, I thought
this issue was settled earlier.

610
00:46:51.384 --> 00:46:53.643
The brick issue was settled.

611
00:46:53.643 --> 00:46:55.416
But not all of you.

612
00:46:55.416 --> 00:46:56.858
But, still...

613
00:46:56.858 --> 00:46:59.264
how can you suddenly fire us like this?

614
00:46:59.264 --> 00:47:02.545
I'm supposed to pay for my daughter's
private academy this month.

615
00:47:02.545 --> 00:47:06.054
If you were worried about that,
you shouldn't have gotten involved.

616
00:47:06.054 --> 00:47:08.197
Why would you take that kid's side?

617
00:47:08.197 --> 00:47:09.822
What were we supposed to do?

618
00:47:09.822 --> 00:47:12.793
He's a young guy with a bright future
and it was an accident.

619
00:47:12.793 --> 00:47:15.384
Should we leave him to get
dragged off for attempted murder?

620
00:47:15.384 --> 00:47:18.152
Why don't you talk to CEO Min for us?

621
00:47:18.152 --> 00:47:20.376
I don't know anything.
That's just how it is.

622
00:47:20.376 --> 00:47:21.753
Don't come tomorrow.

623
00:47:21.753 --> 00:47:24.001
I'm short on labor as it is.

624
00:47:24.001 --> 00:47:26.320
Foreman, Foreman.

625
00:47:26.320 --> 00:47:30.077
Of all the things I've seen in my life,
this is the worst case of abuse.

626
00:47:30.077 --> 00:47:32.385
Hey, you think this is
the only place to work?

627
00:47:32.385 --> 00:47:33.916
It is. This is the only place.

628
00:47:33.916 --> 00:47:36.063
That's why we stuck around here.

629
00:47:36.063 --> 00:47:39.735
Hey, I'll just eat less and live shorter.

630
00:47:39.735 --> 00:47:41.914
I won't bow down to you!

631
00:47:41.914 --> 00:47:46.592
Eat well and live well,
you awful bastards!

632
00:47:46.592 --> 00:47:49.467
What do we do?
Madam Ahn, Mister Kim, Mister Lee.

633
00:47:49.467 --> 00:47:51.994
I should never have brought him around.

634
00:47:51.994 --> 00:47:53.802
I am so sorry.

635
00:47:54.193 --> 00:47:57.144
Why are you sorry?
You don't have to be.

636
00:47:57.664 --> 00:48:00.503
We can find another job.

637
00:48:00.503 --> 00:48:01.856
Yes, yes.

638
00:48:01.856 --> 00:48:05.327
He said it was
because of dandelion seeds.

639
00:48:06.958 --> 00:48:10.690
Even though it was an excuse,
wasn't it cute and naive?

640
00:48:10.690 --> 00:48:14.507
Anyway, they say you should rest
when things go wrong.

641
00:48:14.507 --> 00:48:16.043
Since things have gone wrong...

642
00:48:16.043 --> 00:48:18.445
I'll just rest and look for a new job.

643
00:48:18.445 --> 00:48:20.425
Yeah, don't worry too much.

644
00:48:20.425 --> 00:48:22.681
- Don't worry.
- Yes, yes.

645
00:48:22.681 --> 00:48:25.860
Life is about earning
and living day to day.

646
00:48:25.860 --> 00:48:27.494
Yeah, that's true.

647
00:48:29.150 --> 00:48:30.322
It's okay.

648
00:48:55.277 --> 00:48:56.442
All right.

649
00:49:00.494 --> 00:49:01.675
Okay.

650
00:49:17.731 --> 00:49:20.623
One, two, three.

651
00:49:32.371 --> 00:49:33.416
What is it?

652
00:49:34.385 --> 00:49:38.275
Are you here to beg
on your knees and say sorry?

653
00:49:38.856 --> 00:49:41.094
Kim Ki Sub, Lee Tae Kyung,
and Ahn Mi Yeon...

654
00:49:41.317 --> 00:49:43.235
please reinstate the three of them.

655
00:49:43.896 --> 00:49:45.282
Who are they?

656
00:49:45.282 --> 00:49:47.764
The three people you fired earlier today.

657
00:49:47.764 --> 00:49:49.880
Give them their jobs back.

658
00:49:50.226 --> 00:49:53.947
Otherwise, I'll go through with
my threat on the illegal waste disposal.

659
00:49:53.947 --> 00:49:55.983
I will officially report you.

660
00:49:56.726 --> 00:50:00.333
So, you won't report me
if I give them their jobs back?

661
00:50:02.789 --> 00:50:04.465
You have evidence?

662
00:50:05.001 --> 00:50:07.070
You think I'd come to make a deal
without evidence?

663
00:50:13.485 --> 00:50:16.210
You know that punk
who threw a brick at me?

664
00:50:16.750 --> 00:50:19.211
I hear he's the second son
of Gangsu Group.

665
00:50:21.476 --> 00:50:24.442
I was so shocked by that.

666
00:50:26.572 --> 00:50:28.311
Go on and report me.

667
00:50:28.311 --> 00:50:32.016
I can send him into a cave
with just one call.

668
00:50:33.871 --> 00:50:35.324
Do as you please.

669
00:50:35.324 --> 00:50:37.420
He has nothing to do with me.

670
00:50:37.420 --> 00:50:38.516
Oh...

671
00:50:39.117 --> 00:50:42.177
You don't care even if his life ends?

672
00:50:42.177 --> 00:50:45.137
Getting the jobs of those three people
back is more important to me.

673
00:50:45.137 --> 00:50:46.324
Really?

674
00:50:46.324 --> 00:50:47.922
Yes, it is.

675
00:50:50.996 --> 00:50:53.923
What are you doing with my phone?

676
00:50:54.416 --> 00:50:56.431
Let me go.
I said let me go!

677
00:50:56.431 --> 00:50:58.612
Give it back. Give it back!

678
00:50:58.612 --> 00:50:59.697
There's nothing.

679
00:51:01.137 --> 00:51:02.601
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

680
00:51:03.061 --> 00:51:05.150
I'm sure there's nothing regarding that.

681
00:51:05.985 --> 00:51:07.382
Wow.

682
00:51:09.967 --> 00:51:13.003
You threatened me with a lie?

683
00:51:13.003 --> 00:51:14.744
It's enough just to fire me.

684
00:51:14.744 --> 00:51:17.103
Give the three people their jobs back!

685
00:51:26.670 --> 00:51:29.172
Then tell me where that punk is.

686
00:51:30.050 --> 00:51:32.496
Then I'll give those
three people their jobs back.

687
00:51:33.079 --> 00:51:35.722
Tell me where he is.

688
00:51:38.996 --> 00:51:41.534
Do you understand, kid?

689
00:51:41.882 --> 00:51:44.559
This is a real deal.

690
00:51:50.045 --> 00:51:52.431
I can go out on my own.

691
00:51:55.963 --> 00:51:58.295
How can you throw my phone like that?

692
00:52:01.478 --> 00:52:02.527
Buy a new one.

693
00:52:02.527 --> 00:52:05.416
Use the rest of the money
for candy, you baby.

694
00:52:08.831 --> 00:52:10.907
Hey... hey!

695
00:52:13.291 --> 00:52:16.019
You think money is everything? Hey!

696
00:52:16.019 --> 00:52:17.474
Open the door!

697
00:52:18.143 --> 00:52:21.153
Open the door now. Hey!

698
00:52:43.561 --> 00:52:44.762
Make a decision.

699
00:52:45.572 --> 00:52:48.181
You want to get
their jobs back, or is it him?

700
00:52:53.376 --> 00:52:55.695
Do you think Gangsu Group will stand by

701
00:52:55.695 --> 00:52:58.250
if they know you
threatened Hyuk like this?

702
00:52:58.925 --> 00:53:01.806
You came to ask for their jobs back.

703
00:53:03.074 --> 00:53:04.989
Now you're worried about him?

704
00:53:05.581 --> 00:53:06.786
Who are you?

705
00:53:07.835 --> 00:53:09.568
Are you his girlfriend?

706
00:53:15.579 --> 00:53:17.391
I'm sorry...

707
00:53:18.507 --> 00:53:20.025
Madam Ahn.

708
00:53:20.809 --> 00:53:22.358
Mister Kim.

709
00:53:23.541 --> 00:53:25.213
Mister Lee.

710
00:54:44.307 --> 00:54:45.701
How much do you need?

711
00:54:51.375 --> 00:54:54.054
Tell me. I'll lend it to you.

712
00:54:54.054 --> 00:54:55.338
Why would you?

713
00:54:56.217 --> 00:54:58.688
Who are you to lend me money?

714
00:54:58.688 --> 00:55:00.599
You said you did it for money.

715
00:55:00.599 --> 00:55:02.844
That's why you took a crazy job
like being Hyuk's secretary.

716
00:55:02.844 --> 00:55:05.311
I said I won't do it. I'm quitting.

717
00:55:05.311 --> 00:55:08.402
So, I'll lend it to you.
How much do you need?

718
00:55:10.465 --> 00:55:13.958
Hey... I don't want it.

719
00:55:15.114 --> 00:55:18.204
You run errands for
a third generation rich guy.

720
00:55:18.204 --> 00:55:21.085
I refuse to take money
that's earned like that.

721
00:55:21.085 --> 00:55:22.487
Got it?

722
00:55:45.478 --> 00:55:47.271
Ta-da!

723
00:55:54.822 --> 00:55:56.356
What do you think?

724
00:55:56.356 --> 00:55:57.922
You're surprised, right?

725
00:55:59.088 --> 00:56:00.289
Thanks to you

726
00:56:00.289 --> 00:56:03.949
I was able to know the special sweet
taste of food after working up a sweat.

727
00:56:03.949 --> 00:56:06.789
So, I wanted to give you a gift.

728
00:56:06.789 --> 00:56:09.427
For you, after you've had
a tiresome day...

729
00:56:09.427 --> 00:56:12.269
a romantic and heavenly taste.

730
00:56:17.936 --> 00:56:20.199
These are grade A ribs.

731
00:56:20.199 --> 00:56:23.005
This is the chef, Mister Yoon.

732
00:56:23.005 --> 00:56:26.099
This is wine from the year we were born.

733
00:56:28.465 --> 00:56:32.322
I didn't know which roses
you liked, so I got pink.

734
00:56:32.322 --> 00:56:34.018
There are probably about a thousand.

735
00:56:34.018 --> 00:56:37.393
Quite a lot, right? I know.

736
00:56:38.445 --> 00:56:40.311
Do you like it?

737
00:56:40.311 --> 00:56:42.931
Come here, Joon. Come here.

738
00:56:47.909 --> 00:56:49.934
What's wrong, Joon?

739
00:56:50.646 --> 00:56:54.170
Are those tears
because you're so touched?

740
00:56:54.170 --> 00:56:55.577
Are they not?

741
00:56:55.577 --> 00:56:59.896
Because of a guy who only knows
how to spend his damn money...

742
00:56:59.896 --> 00:57:02.865
Because I was trying to save you...

743
00:57:02.865 --> 00:57:07.516
Because I was trying to hide you,
do you know what I just did?

744
00:57:09.947 --> 00:57:12.733
Joon, what's wrong?
Did something happen?

745
00:57:12.733 --> 00:57:17.275
Mister Kim, who got fired because of you,
has three kids to raise.

746
00:57:17.275 --> 00:57:21.023
Mister Lee pays more than one million won
of his mother's hospital fees a month.

747
00:57:21.023 --> 00:57:25.445
Madam Ahn's husband had a stroke
and she's taking care...

748
00:57:26.005 --> 00:57:30.498
She's taking care of her entire family.

749
00:57:30.498 --> 00:57:31.527
Joon.

750
00:57:31.527 --> 00:57:36.108
This may be nothing
but a lowly job to you.

751
00:57:36.108 --> 00:57:39.407
It was a desperately needed source
of livelihood for them.

752
00:57:39.407 --> 00:57:43.788
They were worried that
you would lose that livelihood!

753
00:57:43.788 --> 00:57:46.358
They put everything on the line.

754
00:57:49.199 --> 00:57:53.266
I thought you would, at least,
have a conscience about that.

755
00:57:53.266 --> 00:57:56.168
Is this all you could think to do?

756
00:57:57.777 --> 00:58:01.525
If they knew they got fired for taking
sides with a some rich troublemaker

757
00:58:01.525 --> 00:58:04.248
they'd feel so taken aback by it all.

758
00:58:10.257 --> 00:58:11.742
To tell you the truth, Joon...

759
00:58:11.742 --> 00:58:14.101
I was thankful to them too.

760
00:58:14.101 --> 00:58:18.262
I prepared an envelope for each of them.

761
00:58:18.262 --> 00:58:19.954
Here.

762
00:58:20.864 --> 00:58:23.492
You think you can
solve everything with money?

763
00:58:23.492 --> 00:58:25.693
Huh? Why not money?

764
00:58:25.693 --> 00:58:28.032
Everyone likes it.

765
00:58:28.032 --> 00:58:32.454
Why did someone like you
appear in front of me?

766
00:58:32.454 --> 00:58:34.199
Why did you show up?

767
00:58:34.199 --> 00:58:37.175
Why did you destroy everything? Why!

768
00:58:37.840 --> 00:58:39.480
Destroy?

769
00:58:39.998 --> 00:58:41.360
I did?

770
00:58:41.360 --> 00:58:42.849
I'm asking you this favor.

771
00:58:42.849 --> 00:58:46.269
Please... please return
to the world you came from.

772
00:58:46.269 --> 00:58:48.389
Stop making things hard
for so many people.

773
00:58:48.389 --> 00:58:50.983
Please just get lost!

774
00:59:15.273 --> 00:59:16.840
Get lost?

775
00:59:46.746 --> 00:59:49.980
Who said you can run this business here?

776
00:59:52.605 --> 00:59:54.188
Who are you people?

777
00:59:54.954 --> 00:59:56.829
Where are you from?

778
00:59:59.465 --> 01:00:01.916
Look here, Baek Sung Ki.

779
01:00:01.916 --> 01:00:05.949
You can't do this
to CEO Byun Gang Su.

780
01:00:05.949 --> 01:00:09.914
You made a living off
of him for this long.

781
01:00:09.914 --> 01:00:15.001
When you left the company,
you got a nice retirement package.

782
01:00:15.001 --> 01:00:18.360
You should be repaying him for that.

783
01:00:19.141 --> 01:00:22.431
Why would you be tackling work
that the head office does?

784
01:00:27.795 --> 01:00:29.338
Take this.

785
01:00:29.338 --> 01:00:34.030
Don't cause a problem
out of this issue anymore.

786
01:00:34.030 --> 01:00:36.507
The CEO...

787
01:00:37.061 --> 01:00:38.925
is watching you.

788
01:00:38.925 --> 01:00:41.336
Stay in line, punk.

789
01:00:49.750 --> 01:00:53.664
Oh, aren't you pretty?

790
01:00:55.778 --> 01:00:57.936
Listen to your dad.

791
01:01:11.641 --> 01:01:13.452
Joon.

792
01:01:13.983 --> 01:01:19.943
Don't make important
decisions in your life...

793
01:01:21.351 --> 01:01:23.789
based on money.

794
01:01:25.010 --> 01:01:29.262
I felt I had no choice and ended up
making a cowardly decision.

795
01:01:29.262 --> 01:01:31.309
But, Joon...

796
01:01:33.851 --> 01:01:36.949
I hope you don't live the way I do.

797
01:02:40.286 --> 01:02:45.693
<i>I was so happy to meet you
that I insisted it was fate.</i>

798
01:02:45.693 --> 01:02:47.990
Stop making things hard
for so many people.

799
01:02:47.990 --> 01:02:50.452
Please just get lost!

800
01:03:25.384 --> 01:03:28.202
You run errands for
a third generation rich guy.

801
01:03:28.202 --> 01:03:30.721
I refuse to take money
that's earned like that.

802
01:03:30.721 --> 01:03:31.940
Got it?

803
01:03:42.836 --> 01:03:45.701
<i>Until you called out my name...</i>

804
01:03:45.701 --> 01:03:50.108
<i>I did not make a single movement.</i>

805
01:04:02.684 --> 01:04:06.119
<i>When you called out my name...</i>

806
01:04:06.119 --> 01:04:11.686
<i>for the first time...
I became a flower.</i>

807
01:04:41.726 --> 01:04:46.523
<i>Please, call me by my name,
which suits my color and fragrance.</i>

808
01:04:46.523 --> 01:04:48.583
<i>Not "third generation rich guy."</i>

809
01:04:48.583 --> 01:04:51.322
What's he saying? Crazy punk.

810
01:05:00.869 --> 01:05:03.914
Hey, have you seen Hyuk?

811
01:05:03.914 --> 01:05:05.719
I don't know.

812
01:05:09.219 --> 01:05:11.286
This was taped here.

813
01:05:15.923 --> 01:05:17.605
What's this?

814
01:05:22.523 --> 01:05:24.128
Here he comes!

815
01:05:29.054 --> 01:05:30.902
Joon!

816
01:05:30.902 --> 01:05:33.802
Joon... look.

817
01:05:48.387 --> 01:05:50.501
<i>I will go to you.</i>

818
01:05:50.501 --> 01:05:52.998
<i>I want to become a flower.</i>

819
01:05:52.998 --> 01:05:55.684
<i>[Appearance of Gangsu Group's
Second Son, Byun Hyuk]</i>

820
01:06:11.708 --> 01:06:13.302
<i>Joon.</i>

821
01:06:13.795 --> 01:06:16.684
<i>I want to become
someone you do not forget.</i>

822
01:06:16.684 --> 01:06:21.206
<i>The one and only glance.</i>

823
01:06:24.750 --> 01:06:31.750
Subtitles by DramaFever

824
01:06:46.503 --> 01:06:50.315
<i>[Revolutionary Love]</i>

825
01:06:50.315 --> 01:06:51.873
<i>What were you thinking?</i>

826
01:06:51.873 --> 01:06:54.356
<i>Is he up to something I don't know
about with Section Chief Kwon?</i>

827
01:06:54.356 --> 01:06:56.260
<i>I looked cool when I went to
the prosecutors, right?</i>

828
01:06:56.260 --> 01:06:57.347
<i>What did Joon say?</i>

829
01:06:57.347 --> 01:06:58.844
<i>Mom, why are doing this to me?</i>

830
01:06:58.844 --> 01:07:01.148
<i>You are so brazen when you come to me.</i>

831
01:07:01.148 --> 01:07:03.242
<i>You make me go crazy.</i>

832
01:07:03.242 --> 01:07:06.001
<i>You're prepared to deal with
not listening to me, right?</i>

833
01:07:06.001 --> 01:07:08.615
<i>- Father!
- How could you this, Honey?</i>

834
01:07:08.615 --> 01:07:10.592
<i>I'm sorry I could not protect you.</i>

835
01:07:10.592 --> 01:07:13.063
<i>Is going to prison all that's left?</i>

836
01:07:13.063 --> 01:07:15.550
<i>Hyuk has to deal with it.
That's the world he lives in.</i>

837
01:07:15.550 --> 01:07:17.929
<i>Live well, third generation rich guy!</i>

